fr.sorbonne_u.components.cyphy.plugins.devs

Interface SimulatorPluginI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.interfaces.EventsExchangingI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.interfaces.ModelDescriptionI, ModelStateAccessI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.interfaces.ParentNotificationI, fr.sorbonne_u.components.PluginI, java.io.Serializable, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.simulators.interfaces.SimulationManagementI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.simulators.interfaces.SimulatorI, SimulatorPluginManagementI
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AtomicSimulatorPluginI, CoordinatorPluginI, RTAtomicSimulatorPluginI, RTCoordinatorPluginI, RTSimulatorPluginI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSimulatorPlugin, AtomicSimulatorPlugin, CoordinatorPlugin, RTAtomicSimulatorPlugin, RTCoordinatorPlugin

    public interface SimulatorPluginI
extends fr.sorbonne_u.components.PluginI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.simulators.interfaces.SimulatorI, SimulatorPluginManagementI, ModelStateAccessI
    The interface SimulatorPluginI declares the core services of the DEVS simulator plug-in.

    Description

    This interface gathers the different interfaces a supervisor plug-in must implement to provide the behaviours required by this role in a DEVS simulation context:

    • SimulatorI declares methods used by other simulator components to perform simulation steps.
    • SimulatorPluginManagementI declares methods used from the supervisor plug-in in order to manage simulation runs by calling the simulators on components holding them.
    • ModelStateAccessI declares methods used by components holding simulation models to access their state during simulation runs when performing software-in-the-loop simulations.

    Invariant

     invariant              true

    Created on : 2018-06-14

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
